<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 4:56PM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow will affect Erie and Crawford Counties
Until 630 PM EST....
At 452 PM EST, radar indicated moderate to heavy wet snow moving
northeast into northwestern Pennsylvania. This will continue into
the evening commute before snow transitions to rain from southwest
to northeast this evening.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Winds to 40 mph...
Visibility dropping to less than three quarters of a mile...
Up to 1 inch of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Erie, Meadville, Corry, Edinboro, Titusville, North East, Union City,
Girard, Cambridge Springs, Waterford, Albion, Linesville, Wattsburg,
Adamsville, Canadohta Lake, Pymatuning Central, Riceville,
Harmonsburg, Northwest Harborcreek, and Lincolnville.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
